# Jira Ticket Management

For any documentation work in this repository, ensure proper Jira ticket tracking.

## Workflow

1. **Check for existing Jira reference** in the user's prompt:
   - Look for Jira issue keys (format: `DOC-123`, `DOC-456`, etc.)
   - Look for Jira links (format: `https://amplitude.atlassian.net/browse/DOC-123`)
   - If found, proceed with the work—no action needed

2. **If no Jira reference exists**, create a new ticket automatically:
   - Use the `mcp_Atlassian_createJiraIssue` tool
   - Set these parameters:
     - `cloudId`: `"https://amplitude.atlassian.net"`
     - `projectKey`: `"DOC"`
     - `issueTypeName`: `"Task"`
     - `summary`: Create a concise summary based on the user's request (under 100 characters)
     - `description`: Provide more details about the documentation task

3. **After ticket creation**:
   - Display the ticket ID clearly (e.g., "DOC-123")
   - Provide the ticket URL
   - Remind the user: "When creating a git branch for this work, include the ticket ID in the branch name (e.g., `DOC-123-update-sdk-docs`)"

## Example Scenarios

### Scenario A: User provides ticket reference
```
User: "Update the SDK docs for DOC-456"
```
✅ Ticket reference found—proceed with the work

### Scenario B: User provides ticket link
```
User: "Update https://amplitude.atlassian.net/browse/DOC-789"
```
✅ Ticket reference found—proceed with the work

### Scenario C: No ticket reference
```
User: "Update the Android SDK documentation to include new features"
```
❌ No ticket found—create new ticket with summary: "Update Android SDK documentation"

## Work logging (required)

Any time you perform substantive work on this repository—editing documentation, creating files, fixing issues, or creating pull requests—append an entry to `AGENT_LOG.md` in the repository root. Log your work at the end of each task, before you finish your response.

### Format

```
| YYYY-MM-DD | Cursor | Short description | PR or commit link |
```

### Rules

- Use today's date in `YYYY-MM-DD` format.
- Set **Submitted By** to `Cursor`.
- Keep the **Short Description** to one brief phrase (under 10 words).
- For **PR Link**: use the full GitHub PR URL if a PR was created, a commit URL if only commits were made, or `N/A` if no commits were made.
- Always append — never overwrite existing entries.
- Log once per task, not once per file edit.

### Examples

```
| 2026-03-12 | Cursor | Fix session replay sampling docs | https://github.com/amplitude/amplitude-docs/pull/1523 |
| 2026-03-12 | Cursor | Apply style rules to SDK docs | N/A |
```

## Notes

- This ensures all documentation work is tracked in Jira.
- Helps the Docs team maintain visibility into ongoing work.
- Supports proper git workflow with ticket IDs in branch names.